        <title>meet customer needs to get ahead of the pack </title>
        <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/aplo/~3/PB0ES9I6fp4/meet-customer-needs-to-get-ahead-of-the-pack-.html" />
        <link rel="replies" type="text/html" href="http://aplo.typepad.com/aplo/2010/08/meet-customer-needs-to-get-ahead-of-the-pack-.html" thr:count="0" />
        <id>tag:typepad.com,2003:post-6a00e54f8dbf5d8833013486737ce6970c</id>
        <published>2010-08-25T12:02:46+01:00</published>
        <updated>2010-08-25T12:00:53+01:00</updated>
        <summary>A blog entry in HBR today outlines three questions companies need to ask themselves to see if they are heading the right direction, that towards the head of the pack. Unsurprisingly question no 1 is: ' Would you say your...</summary>
